The paper deals with fair division of a resource among multiple agents, which is a problem studied in game theory (cs.GT). The authors also analyze the role of partial information in fair division, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The algorithms studied in the paper involve partitioning the resource, which is a problem in data structures (cs.DS). The authors also consider a centralized algorithm for maximizing overall welfare, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
